# The rendered hero video is NOT committed. GitHub renders a video as a
# click-to-play player only when it is uploaded as a PR/issue attachment
# (a user-attachments URL); a repo-committed video renders as a mere download
# link. So the mp4/webm are GitHub-hosted, not stored in git (this also avoids
# multi-MB binary bloat). The committed hero-static.png is the poster /
# click-to-play fallback the README links to.
hero.mp4
hero.webm
hero.gif

# Working-dir render artifacts (regenerable, never committed).
hero-master.mp4
hero-master-noc.mp4
hero-noc.mp4
hero-noc.webm
hero-noc.gif
raw/
fixture/
bach-candidates/
